ormalName="bcNITF2.5" /><DataContent><p>1950 - Uruguayan forward Juan Alberto Schiaffino (C) kicks the ball past Brazilian goalkeeper Moacyr Barbosa to tie the score at 1 during the World Cup final round soccer match between Uruguay and Brazil 16 July 1950 in Rio de Janeiro. Uruguay upset Brazil 2-1 to win its second World title after winning the first World Cup in 1930 in Uruguay. AFP PHOTO</p></DataContent></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Main" /><ContentItem Href="images/main/1950-bra-uru-schiaffino.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="2048" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="1448" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Thumbnail" /><ContentItem Href="images/thumbnail/1950-bra-uru-schiaffino.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="150" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="105" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent><NewsComponent><Role FormalName="Visu" /><ContentItem Href="images/visu/1950-bra-uru-schiaffino.jpg"><MediaType FormalName="Photo" /><Characteristics><Property FormalName="Width" Value="512" /><Property FormalName="Height" Value="362" /></Characteristics></ContentItem></NewsComponent></NewsComponent></NewsComponent></NewsItem></NewsML>